SIMPLE: scraping
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scraping
<hw>Scrap"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of scraping; the act or process of making even, or reducing to the
proper form, by means of a scraper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Something scraped off; that which is separated from
a substance, or is collected by scraping; <as>as, the <ex>scraping</ex>
of the street</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scraping</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Scraping
<hw>Scrap"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Resembling the act of, or the
effect produced by, one who, or that which, scrapes; <as>as, a
<ex>scraping</ex> noise; a <ex>scraping</ex> miser</as>.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Scrap"ing*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scrappily</ent>⟦br⟧
